com.here.android.mpa.mapping

Enum MapOverlayType

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Enum<MapOverlayType>
      • com.here.android.mpa.mapping.MapOverlayType
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Comparable<MapOverlayType>

    public enum MapOverlayType
extends java.lang.Enum<MapOverlayType>
    Represents values describing the display grouping of MapObject objects when added to a Map.

    • Enum Constant Summary

      Enum Constants 
      Enum Constant and Description
      AREA_OVERLAY
      Identifies objects which add information to area features such as heat maps.
      BACKGROUND_OVERLAY
      Identifies objects which are placed directly over (on top or in front of) BACKGROUND_REPLACEMENT objects.
      BACKGROUND_REPLACEMENT
      Identifies objects that replace the background, such as custom satellite data.
      FOREGROUND_OVERLAY
      Identifies objects that are to be placed on top of any other objects.
      POI_OVERLAY
      Identifies objects which augment POI information.
      ROAD_OVERLAY
      Identifies objects which add some information to the road network, such as traffic or GPS location.
      TRANSIT_STOP_OVERLAY
      Identifies objects which augment Transit Stop information.

    • Enum Constant Detail

      • FOREGROUND_OVERLAY

        public static final MapOverlayType FOREGROUND_OVERLAY
        Identifies objects that are to be placed on top of any other objects. These objects appear closer to the viewer than other objects.

      • POI_OVERLAY

        public static final MapOverlayType POI_OVERLAY
        Identifies objects which augment POI information.
        Note:
        Custom raster tiles currently do not support POI_OVERLAY semantic type.

      • TRANSIT_STOP_OVERLAY

        public static final MapOverlayType TRANSIT_STOP_OVERLAY
        Identifies objects which augment Transit Stop information. Transit-related objects have higher priority over street names and other area feature labels.
        Note:
        Custom raster tiles currently do not support TRANSIT_STOP_OVERLAY semantic type.

      • ROAD_OVERLAY

        public static final MapOverlayType ROAD_OVERLAY
        Identifies objects which add some information to the road network, such as traffic or GPS location.

      • AREA_OVERLAY

        public static final MapOverlayType AREA_OVERLAY
        Identifies objects which add information to area features such as heat maps.

      • BACKGROUND_OVERLAY

        public static final MapOverlayType BACKGROUND_OVERLAY
        Identifies objects which are placed directly over (on top or in front of) BACKGROUND_REPLACEMENT objects. Apply this type to custom raster tiles and other map objects that should be drawn on top of the (background) map, but should not hide other objects.

      • BACKGROUND_REPLACEMENT

        public static final MapOverlayType BACKGROUND_REPLACEMENT
        Identifies objects that replace the background, such as custom satellite data. Note that this semantic type does not disable rendering of the background.
